Archery Certification (Level 1)
Date: Sat. Feb. 28, 2015; 9:00 AM - 4:00 PM
Location: North Fork Leadership Center-Archery Field

The National Field Archery Association (NFAA) is a non-profit organization dedicated to the amazing world of archery and they have provided us with an exciting opportunity to learn this sport! This course is offered to all members ages 16 and up.

You will be instructed on proper equipment use, shooting form, safety standards, and learn valuable teaching methods. This course is designed to provide you with valuable leadership skills all while having fun! Your certification will be valid for 3 years.

Special Instructions:
Participants should dress for the weather and wear closed toe shoes (no heels).
Please bring a sack lunch and a water bottle.

Rate: $40.00

Last day to register online is Sun. Feb 22, 2015
